title.narrative: Drainage channels cleaned at least once per year before rainy season in project area
Primary drainage system in Pikine and Guediawaye put it place.
Eligible flood risk reduction community investments completed.
People reached by IEC strategy at local and national level.
Area in peri-urban Dakar protected against recurrent flooding through drainage works
Local flood management committees in Pikine and Guediawaye are engaged in stormwater management activities.

target.value: COLIGEP action plans implemented and evaluated

actual.value: 9 committees created (COLIGEP) in collaboration with the local collectivities to ensure efficiency, capacity building program andrelated action plan adopted and on ongoing implementation including trainings and equipment.

title.narrative: Tools related to urban resilience including climate change, adopted

baseline.value: No Tools related to urban resilience including climate change, adopted

target.value: Tools related to urban resilience including climate change, adopted

actual.value: A national strategy for integrated urban management and planning addressing, inter-alia, flood prevention and climate changeimpacts has been validated by the project technical committee and adopted by the National Urban Committee under the leadership ofthe Urban Ministry

title.narrative: Experience in "inter-municipal sustainable city" practices, through concerted territorial development (CTD), improved

baseline.value: No experience in inter-municipal "sustainable and resilient city" practices, through concerted territorial development improved

target.value: At least one session per cooperation framework held on cities sustainability management

actual.value: For Saint-Louis sustainable city pilot project a 3 years program of activities for the development of inter-communality cooperationfor the city sustainability has been prepared and implementation is ongoing

title.narrative: AN O&M stormwater drainage management system in Pikine and Guediawaye is functional.

target.value: OM system in Pikine and Guediawaye functional.

actual.value: The sudies were validated, and the creation of a Fund was convened on. The sanitation fund decree is still on process for signing.However, the MoF didn't allocate funding for O&M to ONAS this FY. To resolve current O&M problems both ONAS and the MunicipalDevelopment Agency (ADM) agreed to hire contractors, from the project funding, to operate the maintenance needs.

title.narrative: Key stakeholders (persons) trained in flood risk management, urban climate change resilience and territorial planning
